target: game_loop
validations:
  - name: loop_starts_and_renders
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the game starts and the main loop is running. The HTML page
        should load without console errors, a canvas element should be visible,
        and the game should be rendering frames. The tile grid should be drawn
        on the canvas and the tick counter should be advancing.
  - name: pause_and_resume
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the game can be paused and resumed. Pressing the P key
        should freeze the simulation — the tick counter should stop advancing
        and entity positions should not change. Pressing P again should resume
        the simulation. While paused, the canvas should still render (not go
        blank) and the player should still be able to interact with UI menus.
  - name: speed_control
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the simulation speed can be changed. Pressing 1, 2, or 4
        should set the game speed to normal, fast, or ultra respectively. At
        higher speeds the simulation should visibly advance faster — visitors
        move more quickly and the tick counter increments at a higher rate.
        The game should remain stable at all speed settings without visual
        glitches or freezes.
